 Your post demonstrates your total unfamiliarity with Canadian law, particularly as it applies to hate speech.  Hate speech is defined in the Criminal Code of Canada as any communication which has the following characteristics:   it contains references or calls for violence against an identifiable group  the content of the communication tends to promote or incite violence against the group  the communication is made via a medium that is used or directed towards making the group more vulnerable to violence Such a communication could be considered a "terrorist" or "extremist" propaganda piece, or simply your typical internet ranting.     <BOS>  Write a neutral comment mentioning christian people: "Jesus is more about love than about rules. He was not a priest and did not write the bible"  There's no denying Jesus was a great prophet, but love cannot be legislated. Rules and laws can be broken, but the love of God cannot be
