 Islamaphobia?  The author clearly doesn't understand the term.  Islamaphobia is fear of Islamic doctrine and practice, typically (but not always) couched in terms of Islamophobia.   The reason for the motion is that a significant minority of Canadians are fearful of the ideology and practice of the so-called "Islamaphobia" of islam.  The motion is intended to combat this type of prejudice, which is not an irrational fear.  The motion should pass with little or no debate, but it may go some way to combat the irrational prejudices that seem to be fostered in Canada by a relatively small but vocal minority of the population.    Islamaphobia does not exist.  Fear of islam exists.   What is not reasonable is for fear of islam to be used as a pretext to persecute a particular religious group.     <BOS>  Write a neutral comment mentioning
