 You have a point, but you also appear to ignore some important historical facts.  The first Crusade, which was led by Pope Urban II in 1095, was intended to end the raids by the Muslim raiders known as the Seljuk Turks from the East that had been ravaging and destroying the Christian kingdoms in the Middle East for centuries.  The Seljuk Turks were originally from the Black Sea region, but had fought their way through Turkey, reaching the southern reaches of Greece and the eastern fringes of the Ottoman Empire in the 13th century.    The Christians of Syria, Lebanon, and Jordan had been under Seljuk rule since the 7th century; the Turks had never been in Syria, Lebanon, or Jordan before that.    The Crusaders were led by Pope Urban II and the military leader, Albert, in an effort to reclaim the Holy Land for Christ from the Seljuk Turks
